<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1930-10-11T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1930-10-11T16:00:00-05:00" n="263" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d263">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">810.154/253: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the Minister in Honduras</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Lay</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1930-10-11T16:00:00-05:00">October 11, 1930—4
                                p.m.</date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>61. Please telegraph as soon as possible response to request in last
                            paragraph of mail instruction 40, dated October 1.</p>
                        <p>The Legation at Panama telegraphs that engineers can begin survey in
                            Honduras about November first.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Castle</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>